roeber@vxcrna.cern.ch writes:

>Well, you're only mapping each plaintext into one of 2^64 cyphertexts,
>so the 112 bit key really only has 64 bits of information.  Adding more
>key won't help.

The number of functions of 2^64 plaintexts into 2^64 crypted texts is 
2^64!, whihc has at least 2^64 bits of information, not 64. So in
principle, you could use a key 2^64 bits long profitably ( as I believe
it is now known that multiple DES does cover the whole space of
functions).

